The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, March 15, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, March 15, 2003				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Attend Bhakti, a vocal recital by Sarmila Bose, presented by CIMA Adda, at CIMA Gallery at 6 pm on Sunday.				 																Colours of celebration				 																																	Have a gala time with Indipop bands, Ghoomer dance, Rajasthani dhap, colours and thandai at Fun City on Sunday.				 																																	Laugh your heart out at a pre-Holi Hasya Kavi Sammelan at Space Circle at 6.30 pm.				 																Play time				 																																	Book your seats for Koi Ek Raat, a play staged by Spandan, at Gyan Manch at 6.30 pm on Sunday.				 																Brush with culture				 																																	Enjoy a programme of music and poetry-reading at Swabhumi from 4 pm.				 																																	Drop in at the Academy of Fine Arts, North Gallery, for the second group exhibition of Howrah Paints.
